      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries </strong>to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined tray with the <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>smoky fries</strong></p>",
